 A local educational agency (as defined in 


    20 U.S.C. 7801


), system of vocational education, or other school system;

 Afford a qualified handicapped person an opportunity to participate
in or benefit from the aid, benefit or services that is not equal to
that afforded others;

 The overall size of the recipient's program or activity with
respect to number of employees, number and type of facilities, and
size of budget;

 Supervisors and managers may be informed regarding restrictions on
the work or duties of handicapped persons and regarding necessary
accommodations;

 Making physical alterations which enable handicapped persons to
have access to otherwise inaccessible areas or features of historic
properties;

 Identify physical obstacles in the recipient's facilities that
limit the accessibility of its program or activity to handicapped
persons;
